# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be:
#   feat     (new feature)
#   fix      (bug fix)
#   docs     (changes to documentation)
#   style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#   refactor (refactoring production code)
#   test     (adding tests, refactoring tests; no production code change)
#   chore    (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc; no production code change)
#   perf     (performance improvements)
#   ci       (CI/CD pipeline changes)
#
# Scope can be:
#   mobile   (mobile app changes)
#   core     (rust core engine changes)
#   ai       (AI integration changes)
#   ux       (user experience changes)
#   infra    (infrastructure changes)
#   docs     (documentation changes)
#   agents   (sub-agent system changes)
#
# Subject should use imperative mood: "fix bug" not "fixed bug"
# Body should explain what and why vs. how
# Footer should contain any BREAKING CHANGE or issue references